<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>MindShelf Privacy Policy</title>
  <style>
    :root {
      --bg: #0b130f;
      --card: #121f18;
      --sage: #9fbda7;
      --text: #fff8ec;
      --muted: #9aa39d;
      --line: rgba(255, 248, 236, 0.12);
      --danger: #e56f5f;
    }

    * {
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "SF Pro Display", "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at top right, rgba(159, 189, 167, 0.18), transparent 32%),
        var(--bg);
      color: var(--text);
      line-height: 1.65;
    }

    main {
      width: min(860px, 92%);
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 72px 0;
    }

    .brand {
      font-family: Georgia, "Times New Roman", serif;
      font-size: 28px;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin-bottom: 80px;
      color: var(--text);
    }

    .eyebrow {
      color: var(--muted);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.18em;
      font-size: 14px;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }

    h1 {
      font-family: Georgia, "Times New Roman", serif;
      font-size: clamp(44px, 8vw, 82px);
      line-height: 0.95;
      margin: 0 0 24px;
      color: var(--text);
    }

    .intro {
      max-width: 640px;
      font-size: 20px;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin-bottom: 42px;
    }

    .card {
      background: rgba(18, 31, 24, 0.88);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 28px;
      padding: 34px;
      box-shadow: 0 24px 60px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.22);
      backdrop-filter: blur(14px);
    }

    section {
      padding: 26px 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    }

    section:last-child {
      border-bottom: none;
      padding-bottom: 0;
    }

    h2 {
      font-family: Georgia, "Times New Roman", serif;
      font-size: 30px;
      margin: 0 0 12px;
      color: var(--text);
    }

    p, li {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 17px;
    }

    ul {
      margin: 12px 0 0;
      padding-left: 22px;
    }

    a {
      color: var(--sage);
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    .pill {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-top: 20px;
      padding: 10px 16px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: rgba(159, 189, 167, 0.16);
      color: var(--sage);
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    footer {
      color: var(--muted);
      margin-top: 28px;
      font-size: 14px;
      text-align: center;
    }

    @media (max-width: 600px) {
      main {
        padding: 44px 0;
      }

      .brand {
        margin-bottom: 52px;
      }

      .card {
        padding: 24px;
        border-radius: 22px;
      }

      h2 {
        font-size: 25px;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <main>
    <div class="brand">MindShelf</div>

    <div class="eyebrow">Privacy Policy</div>
    <h1>Your shelf stays yours.</h1>
    <p class="intro">
      MindShelf helps you save books, notes, quotes, and reflections. This policy explains what information is collected and how it is used.
    </p>

    <div class="card">
      <section>
        <h2>Effective Date</h2>
        <p>April 2026</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>MindShelf may collect the following information when you use the app:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Email address and account login information</li>
          <li>Books added to your shelf</li>
          <li>Notes, quotes, reflections, and ideas you create</li>
          <li>Basic technical information such as app version, device type, diagnostics, and crash data if enabled</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
        <p>We use your information to provide the core app experience, including account access, syncing your shelf, saving your notes, improving reliability, and responding to support requests.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>MindShelf may use Firebase and Google Cloud services for authentication, data storage, and app infrastructure. If book search is enabled, MindShelf may use the Google Books API to help users discover books.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
        <p>We do not sell your personal data. Data is only shared with service providers necessary to operate MindShelf.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Data Security</h2>
        <p>We use reasonable technical measures to protect your information. However, no online service can guarantee absolute security.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Account Deletion</h2>
        <p>You may delete your account from within the app settings where supported, or contact us to request deletion of your account and associated data.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Children’s Privacy</h2>
        <p>MindShelf is not intended for children under 13.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Changes</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any updates will be posted on this page.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>For privacy questions, contact us at:</p>
        <p><a href="mailto:YOUR_EMAIL_HERE">YOUR_EMAIL_HERE</a></p>
        <span class="pill">MindShelf — Read & Remember</span>
      </section>
    </div>

    <footer>© 2026 MindShelf. All rights reserved.</footer>
  </main>
</body>
</html>
